What are people's first thoughts on Arkadeo?

I do not approve.Arkadeo definitely feels like a money grab. There are too many modes and (unless you're a paying member) too few to do well in anything.

The Level-Up Mode is a ripoff, plain and simple. I will explain in a more detailed post later on.

I like the idea of emphasizing versatility in the League Mode, but with the high number of games relative to the amount of free plays awarded to players, it's quite hard to do well in the upper tiers without buying s (or having access to unlimited s during the beta... ) Once you reach the Silver tier or higher, you can be demoted if you're ranked too low by the end of a period. Of course, both of these contribute to M-T's primary objective of encouraging you to buy s...

Mission Mode is redundant because your scores (for score-based objectives) don't count towards the League, and your level-ups (for level-based objectives) don't count towards jackpots. The payouts are meager and not worth the trouble. Lastly, your progress is not saved: you restart from Mission 1 every period.

And yes, there are definitely too many games that lack originality...

My second RNG had a decent lineup that included hyenas (though not at the outset), and I thought there was practically no way I could fail to break 43.2k. After all, from to (that's multiple plays in this tier), I had never spent more than 3 s to break 50k.

Well, I overestimated my Animoz skills. After 28 minutes, at 23:12 CET, I finished with 41 100 pts. I was still 4 classification points away from 3rd place. With 18 minutes left, starting a 3rd Animoz game was out of the question. (I learned the hard way that your score may fail to register if you finish a game after 23:30)

I was on my last 2 free s, and I really didn't want to spend an MTPass. What choices did I have left?

I looked at the standings. My lowest-ranking games were Pulsar (#21), Nosushi (#19) and FAFI (#17). I was (and still am) no good at any of the timed action games, so Pulsar and FAFI were out of the question.

I decided to bet everything on Nosushi, despite the very real risk of losing all of my hard work over the last 13 days. At this point, the primary issue had shifted from the debate over buying s to the fact that 23:30 was rapidly approaching. With no time left to make complex calculations or simulate moves in MS Paint (as I often do with untimed puzzle games), I relied purely on gut feelings to make my moves. The first one didn't go so well. Then, at 23:20, I struck the jackpot with my very last free of the season, and finished with 67 940 pts.

I probably posted more details than most of you would care to know, but that's basically what happened.
